\id EPH - Plain English Version 
\h Ephesians 
\toc3 Ephesians 
\toc2 Ephesians 
\toc1 Paul’s Letter to the Ephesians 
\mt1 The letter that Paul wrote to the Christians at Ephesus  
\mt2 (The book in the Holy Bible called \bk Ephesians\bk*)  
\imt1 About this letter  
\ip Paul wrote this letter about 2,000 years ago, about 30 years after Jesus went back to heaven, and it is now part of the Holy Bible.  
\ip God sent Paul to lots of countries and lots of towns to tell people about Jesus. One of those towns was Ephesus (see Acts 18:19—20:1). It was a big town in the country that is now called Turkey. About 200 years later the enemies of Ephesus broke it down, and today there are just stones and rubbish at that place in Turkey.  
\ip At the time when Paul wrote this letter, the people called the Romans were the bosses over lots of nations. The Roman bosses didn’t like Paul telling people about Jesus, so they grabbed him and put him in jail. Paul wrote this letter while he was in that jail, in Rome.  
\ip In this letter, Paul wrote about how God planned great things for us Christians. He wrote about how Jesus joins all of us together into his family, no matter what nation we belong to, so that we can be strong for God and live the way he wants us to live.  
\ip Paul wrote this letter a long time ago, but it still has good messages for us today. So we have to take notice today of those messages that Paul wrote to the Christians at Ephesus.  
\cl Chapter  
\c 1  
\p
